snippet: An Iraqi named Wissam Najm Abd Zayd al Zubaydi and known as Abu Nabil — was targeted Nov. 13 in a United States airstrike on a compound in the eastern city of Derna.
abstract: Pentagon announces Wissam Najm Abd Zayd al Zubaydi, senior leader of Islamic State group in Libya who was also known as Abu Nabil, was killed in November airstrike; strike was first attack against Islamic State leader in Libya carried out by United States.
lead_paragraph: An Iraqi named Wissam Najm Abd Zayd al Zubaydi and known as Abu Nabil — was targeted Nov. 13 in a United States airstrike on a compound in the eastern city of Derna.

headline.main: Libya: Pentagon Confirms Death of an ISIS Leader
headline.print_headline: Africa; Libya: Pentagon Confirms Death of an ISIS Leader Attacked by the U.S.
